name: Horimon 004 鳳凰;PHOENIX
description:
Meaning : Beauty, Elegance, Peace, Love

Ho-Oh translates as phoenix but technically they are a bit different. The European phoenix is a fire bird which never dies, but the Asian Ho-Oh is a bird that looks like a peacock and is very colorful. Ho-Oh is believed to appear before something very good happening. Therefore, Ho-Oh is a symbol of luckiness and happiness. Ho-Oh is also an ambisexual bird, having both male and female in one body making Ho-Oh a symbol of peaceful marriage.
